    <title>RADCore</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="namespaceRADCore" kindref="compound">RADCore</ref> is the foundation module. It provides the event system, connection handles, event loops, timers, cross-thread invocation helpers, IODevice, memory buffers, files, binary data streams, JSON, settings, filesystem utilities, process/PTY handling, thread pool/future helpers, and compact value primitives.</para>
<para>Beta notes:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1EventLoop" kindref="compound">RADCore::EventLoop</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1Connection" kindref="compound">RADCore::Connection</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1Timer" kindref="compound">RADCore::Timer</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADIODevice" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADIODevice</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADFile" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADFile</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADBuffer" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADBuffer</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADDataStream" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADDataStream</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADJsonDocument" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADJsonDocument</ref></computeroutput>, and <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADSettings" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADSettings</ref></computeroutput> are the primary foundation APIs.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>File watching and process/PTY helpers are Linux-first in this beta. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
